d by Rico Love]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Kanye West]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Best Night of My Life\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[Jamie Foxx]]\n| cover      = Jamiefoxxbestnightofmylife.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = December 21, 2010\n| recorded   = 2009{{ndash}}2010\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[hip hop music|hip hop]]}}\n| length     = 55:07\n| label      = [[J Records|J]]\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[The Y's]]|[[Bink (producer)|Bink]]|[[Tony \"Chef Tone\" Scales]]|[[Danja (musician)|Danja]]|[[Rico Love]]|[[Noah \"40\" Shebib]]|[[Malay (producer)|Malay]]|[[Kawan \"KP\" Prather|KP]]|[[Eric Hudson]]|Mel & Mus|Big Bob|Juke|Jamie Foxx}}\n| prev_title = [[Intuition (Jamie Foxx album)|Intuition]]\n| prev_year  = 2008\n| next_title = [[Hollywood: A Story of a Dozen Roses]]\n| next_year  = 2015\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Best Night of My Life\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = [[Winner (Jamie Foxx song)|Winner]]\n | single1date = April 6, 2010<ref name=\"apple2\"/>\n | single2     = [[Living Better Now]]\n | single2date = November 2, 2010\n | single3     = [[Fall for Your Type]]\n | single3date = November 12, 2010\n | single4     = Best Night of My Life\n | single4date = April 5, 2011<ref name=\"webcitation.org\">{{cite web |url=http://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases |title=WebCite query |publisher=Webcitation.org |accessdate=2012-06-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5xj7B1SFb?url=http://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases |archivedate=April 5, 2011 }}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Best Night of My Life'''''<ref name=\"rap-up.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2010/11/18/jamie-foxx-renames-album-sets-release-date/ |title=Jamie Foxx Renames Album, Sets Release Date |publisher=Rap-Up.com |date=2010-11-18 |accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/960687/jamie-foxx-album-preview |title=Jamie Foxx Album Preview: ''Body'' |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard.com]] |first=Mariel |last=Consepcion |date=January 12, 2010 |accessdate=July 15, 2010}}</ref> is the fourth [[studio album]] by American singer and actor [[Jamie Foxx]]. It was released on December 21, 2010, by [[J Records]]. The album debuted at number six on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart. Upon its release, ''Best Night of My Life'' was met with generally mixed reviews from [[music critics]].  The album has sold 409,000 copies in the US as of January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150130035055/http://hitsdailydouble.com/new_album_releases|archivedate= January 30, 2015 |url=http://hitsdailydouble.com/new_album_releases |title=Upcoming Releases |website=Hits Daily Double |publisher=HITS Digital Ventures }}</ref> ''Best Night of My Life'' was supported by four singles in total; \"[[Winner (Jamie Foxx song)|Winner]]\" featuring [[Justin Timberlake]] and [[T.I.]], \"[[Living Better Now]]\" featuring [[Rick Ross]], \"Fall for Your Type\" featuring [[Drake (rapper)|Drake]] and \"Best Night of My Life\" featuring [[Wiz Khalifa]].\n\n== Background ==\nThe album was originally scheduled to be released under the title ''Body''.\n\n== Promotion ==\nOn November 16, 2009, the song titled \"Speak French\" featuring [[Gucci Mane]], was released as the buzz single.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/speak-french/id339189253?i=339189391&ign-mpt=uo%3D4 |title=Speak French (feat. Gucci Mane) - Single |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=2009-11-16 |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n\n== Singles ==\n\"[[Winner (Jamie Foxx song)|Winner]]\" featuring [[Justin Timberlake]] and [[T.I.]], was released as the album's lead single on April 6, 2010.<ref name=\"apple2\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/winner-feat-justin-timberlake/id364682022 |title=Winner (featuring Justin Timberlake & T.I.) - Single by Jamie Foxx - Download Winner (featuring Justin Timberlake & T.I.) - Single on iTunes |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |accessdate=April 9, 2010}}</ref>\n\nThe album's second single \"[[Living Better Now]]\" featuring [[Rick Ross (rapper)|Rick Ross]] was released as a digital download on November 2, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0049XLVIO |title=Living Better Now: Jamie Foxx featuring Rick Ross and The Notorious B.I.G.: MP3 Downloads |date= |accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref> It officially impacted Rhythmic and Urban radio in the US on November 9, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases |title=Top 40 Rhythmic Future Releases &#124; R&B Song and Hip-Hop Music Release Dates &#124; |publisher=Allaccess.com |date= |accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/urban/future-releases |title=Urban/UAC Future Releases &#124; R&B, Hip Hop, Release Schedule and Street Dates &#124; |publisher=Allaccess.com |date= |accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref>\n\n\"[[Fall For Your Type]]\" featuring [[Drake (rapper)|Drake]], was released as the album third single on November 12, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/fall-for-your-type-feat-drake/id403387871 |title=Fall for Your Type (featuring Drake) - Single by Jamie Foxx - Download Fall for Your Type (featuring Drake) - Single on iTunes |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=2010-11-12 |accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref>\n\n\"Best Night of My Life\" featuring [[Wiz Khalifa]], was released as the album's fourth single on April 5, 2011.<ref name=\"webcitation.org\"/>\n\n=== Promotional singles ===\n\"Yep Dat's Me\" featuring [[Ludacris]] and [[Soulja Boy]], was released as the album's first promotional single on December 17, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B004FXCI1M |title=Yep Dat's Me [Explicit&#93;: Jamie Foxx Featuring Ludacris & Soulja Boy: MP3 Downloads |date= |accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref> Another version of the song, which features [[T.I.]] was released as well.\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| MC = 58/100<ref name=\"Metacritic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/best-night-of-my-life/jamie-foxx |title=Best Night of My Life Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=2014-04-06}}</ref>\n| rev1      = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|3|5}} <ref>{{cite web|last=Jeffries |first=David |url=https://allmusic.com/album/best-night-of-my-life-r1692050 |title=Best Night of My Life - Jamie Foxx : Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards |publisher=AllMusic |date=2010-12-21 |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n|rev2=''[[The Boston Globe]]''|rev2Score= mixed <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boston.com/ae/music/cd_reviews/articles/2011/01/03/jamie_foxx_best_night_of_my_life/ |title=Jamie Foxx, 'Best Night of My Life' |publisher=Boston.com |date=2011-01-03 |accessdate=2012-08-21}}</ref>\n|rev3= ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''|rev3Score= B\u2212 <ref>{{cite web|author=Mikael Wood |url=https://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20455849,00.html |title=Best Night of My Life Review &#124; Music Reviews and News |publisher=EW.com |date=2010-12-30 |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n|rev4= [[HipHopDX]]|rev4Score= {{Rating|3.5|5}} <ref>{{cite web|last=Bassa |first=Amanda |url=http://www.hiphopdx.com/index/album-reviews/id.1602/title.jamie-foxx-best-night-of-my-life |title=Jamie Foxx - Best Night Of My Life &#124; Read Hip Hop Reviews, Rap Reviews & Hip Hop Album Reviews |publisher=HipHop DX |date=2011-01-04 |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n|rev5= ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''|rev5Score= {{Rating|2.5|4}} <ref>{{cite web|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2010/12/album-review-jamie-foxxs-the-best-night-of-my-life.html |title=Album review: Jamie Foxx's 'The Best Night of My Life' |publisher=Latimesblogs.latimes.com |date=2010-12-21 |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n|rev6= ''[[The New York Times]]'' |rev6Score=(favorable) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/04/arts/music/04choice.html?_r=1 |title=Jamie Foxx, Ciara, Greyson Chance, Cody Simpson - Reviews |publisher=NYTimes.com |date= |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n|rev7= [[PopMatters]]|rev7Score= (2/10) <ref>{{cite web|last=Amidon |first=David |url=https://www.popmatters.com/pm/review/135929-jamie-foxx-best-night-of-my-life/ |title=Jamie Foxx: Best Night of My Life < PopMatters |publisher=Popmatters.com |date= |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n|rev8= ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' |rev8Score={{Rating|3|5}} <ref>{{cite web|author=Jonah Weiner |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/best-night-of-my-life-20101221 |title=Best Night of My Life &#124; Album Reviews |publisher=Rolling Stone |date=2010-12-21 |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n|rev9= [[Slant Magazine]] |rev9Score={{Rating|2.5|5}} <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/jamie-foxx-best-night-of-my-life/2352 |title=Jamie Foxx: Best Night of My Life 2 &#124; Music Review |publisher=Slant Magazine |date= |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n|rev10= ''[[USA Today]]'' |rev10Score={{Rating|2.5|4}} <ref>{{cite web|last=Jones |first=Steve |url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/music/reviews/2010-12-21-listen21_ST_N.htm |title=Listen Up: Keyshia Cole, Jamie Foxx, Keri Hilson, Ghostface Killah |publisher=Usatoday.Com |date=2010-12-21 |accessdate=2012-06-13}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Best Night of My Life'' was met with generally mixed reviews from [[music critics]]. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[Normalization (statistics)|normalized]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album received an [[average]] score of 58, which indicates \"mixed or average reviews\", based on 9 reviews. In a mixed review, David Jeffries of [[Allmusic]] wrote that, \"If ''Best Night of My Life'' is just part of the bigger Foxx picture, rather than an item from his sideline career, it\u2019s still an above-average celebrity album\".\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column    = Producer(s)\n| title1          = This Will Be (Intro)\n| writer1         = [[The Independents (vocal group)|Chuck Jackson]], [[The Independents (vocal group)|Marvin Yancy]]\n| length1         = 1:41\n| title2          =  Best Night of My Life\n| note2           = featuring [[Wiz Khalifa]]\n| writer2         = [[Eric Hudson]], Eric Bishop, Breyon Prescott, [[Tony \"Chef Tone\" Scales|Tony Scales]], Cameron Thomaz\n| extra2 = Hudson\n| length2         =  3:05\n| title3          = [[Living Better Now]]\n| note3           = featuring [[Rick Ross]]\n| writer3         =  [[Bink (producer)|Bink]], [[Ernie Isley]], [[Marvin Isley]], [[O'Kelly Isley]], [[Ronald Isley]], [[Rudolph Isley]], Christopher Jasper, [[Rico Love]], Prescott, William Roberts II, Bishop, [[Tony \"Chef Tone\" Scales]]\n| extra3 =   [[Bink (producer)|Bink]]\n| length3         = 4:06\n| title4          = [[Winner (Jamie Foxx song)|Winner]]\n| note4           = featuring [[Justin Timberlake]] & [[T.I.]]\n| writer4         = [[James Fauntleroy II]], [[Justin Timberlake]], Robert Knox, [[T.I.|Clifford Harris, Jr.]]\n| extra4 = [[The Y's]]\n| length4         = 4:02\n| title5          = Freak\n| note5           = featuring [[Rico Love]]\n| writer5         = [[Danja (musician)|Danja]], Love, [[Marcella Araica]]\n| extra5 = Danja\n| length5         = 4:34\n| title6          = Hit It Like This\n| note6           = \n| writer6         = Melvin Hough II, Prescott, Rivelino Raoul Wouter \n| extra6 = Mel & Mus\n| length6         = 2:48\n| title7          = Yep Dat's Me\n| note7           = featuring [[Ludacris]] & [[Soulja Boy]]\n| writer7         = Hudson, Bishop, [[Lonny Bereal]], [[Michael Dion]] ,Christopher Bridges, James Smith\n| extra7 = Hudson, [[Ezekiel Lewis]]*\n| length7         = 3:07\n| title8          = [[Fall for Your Type]]\n| note8           = featuring [[Drake (entertainer)|Drake]]\n| writer8         = [[Noah \"40\" Shebib]], Noel Campbell, Aubrey Graham\n| extra8 = Noah \"40\" Shebib, [[Drake (rapper)|Drake]] (co.)\n| length8         = 4:30\n| title9          = Gorgeous\n| writer9     